The paper discusses a novel synthesis of cognitive psychology and neural cell assembly modeling, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper introduces a new representational format for analyzing tasks, which is relevant to Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the advantages of using neural models over symbolic artificial intelligence production systems, which is relevant to the Cognitive Psychology (cs.COG) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes the potential for a new general theory of psychology and neurophysiology, which is relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
